ot\in\mathbb{Q}$, then the solutions are algebraically independent over $\mathbb{C}$, that is $tr.deg_{\mathbb{C}}\mathbb{C}(x_1,y_1,\ldots,x_n,y_n)=2n$. As a main part of the proof, we show that the set defined by the system in universal differential fields, with $ rac{d}{b}
